Two teenagers have been arrested after hundreds of cannabis plants with an estimated street value of Â£150,000 were discovered in Inverclyde. Teenagers held after cannabis farm found in Kilmacolm Two teenagers have been arrested after hundreds of cannabis plants with an estimated street value of &pound;150,000 were discovered in Inverclyde.
A spokeswoman for Police Scotland said about 350 plants were found at premises on Gryffe Road, Kilmacolm, at about 13:00 on 19 September.
Two 16-year-old males were arrested in connection with the discovery.
The spokeswoman said they were scheduled to appear in court earlier this week.
 